{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778260836,"nonce":"mWlgNW0MSP/atlCqBKID8qG3qpY=","title":"Linear regulator and linear tracker baselines for decoupling acid test","message":"Stage 2 in the proposed regulator-coupling / decoupling-chain programme (exploration, not committed). Depends on stage 1 (4469cae) for a clean evaluation pipeline.\n\n**Question.** Is Δv \u003e 0 a property of linear regulators specifically (Gemini's claim), or of any controller trained against this loss? This is the sharpest operational test of the decoupling hypothesis.\n\n**Architecture variants** (all trained with the same pipeline: C\u0026S-faithful Q schedule, full-state ε adversary from issue TBD, 600 ms horizon):\n1. **Linear regulator** `u_t = -K_t · x_t`, K_t a learned LTV gain. Mirrors Riccati functional form.\n2. **Linear tracker** `u_t = u_ff(t) - K_t · (x_t - x_nom(t))`, both `u_ff(t)` and `K_t` learned LTV. Same expressivity plus an explicit feedforward channel.\n3. **Affine recurrent controller** with a single linear hidden state.\n4. **Full GRU** (180 hidden) as control.\n\n**Infrastructure note.** The linear-regulator and linear-tracker share parameter definitions, training loop, and Δv evaluation; they should be implemented together. The tracker's `u_ff(t)` and `K_t` are both learned LTV; the ratio `||u_ff||_∞ / ||K_t · x_nom||_∞` across reach time is a diagnostic for how much feedforward is actually used.\n\n**Discriminator prediction.** If Gemini's mechanism is right: regulator (variant 1) ≈ +Δv, tracker (variant 2) ≈ 0, GRU ≈ 0. If variants 1 and 2 split sign cleanly, decoupling-via-parameterisation is the best explanation. If both give +Δv, the feedforward channel does not enable decoupling. If both give ≈ 0, the \"linear regulator inflates velocity\" claim is not robust to this training protocol.\n\n**PGD inner-step count sweep.** At stage 2, sweep PGD inner steps {5, 20, 50} to check adversary convergence (per killable-risk in plan §7; cross-ref 89891ab).\n\n**Cross-refs.** Plan §3 stage 2. Eval-pipeline audit 4469cae. Adversary-class issue (full-state ε, stage 4). Training-methods coord c99ad9d.","files":null}]}